---
import TipsTableOfContents from "@/components/TipsTableOfContents";
import DashboardLayout from "@/layouts/DashboardLayout.astro";
import SubHeader from "@/layouts/SubHeader.astro";

const headingStyle = "text-3xl py-4";
const sectionStyle = "flex flex-col";
const paragraphStyle = "mb-6";
const imageWidth = 300;
---

<DashboardLayout title="Tips & Tricks">
  <div class="flex flex-row gap-4 pb-16">
    <div class="container flex flex-col w-full max-w-2xl gap-6 py-4 mx-auto">
      <SubHeader title="Tips & Tricks" />

      <hr />
      <TipsTableOfContents />
      <hr class="lg:hidden" />

      <section id="configuration" class={sectionStyle}>
        <h1 class={headingStyle}>Overview</h1>
        <p class={paragraphStyle}>
          There are a couple of options menus in Hiddify, I'll be covering the most important ones here.
        </p>
        <img src="/tips/config.png" alt="Configuration" width={imageWidth / 1.5} class="self-center" loading="lazy" />
        <img
          src="/tips/proxy-config.png"
          alt="proxy"
          width={imageWidth / 1.5}
          class="self-center pt-4"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </section>

      <hr />

      <section id="proxies" class={sectionStyle}>
        <h1 class={headingStyle}>Proxies</h1>
        <p class={paragraphStyle}>
          By default, the app will automatically choose the proxy with the lowest ping. However, if
          streaming/downloading feels slow, I recommend manually selecting proxies with 'WS CDN Vless' or 'WS CDN
          Vmess'.
          <br />
          <br />
          Both of these, in my experience, have pretty fast download speeds. There isn't much difference between tls and
          tls_h2.
        </p>
        <img src="/tips/proxy.png" alt="proxy" width={imageWidth} class="self-center" loading="lazy" />
      </section>

      <hr />

      <section id="options" class={sectionStyle}>
        <h1 class={headingStyle}>Config options</h1>
        <p class={paragraphStyle}>
          For Remote DNS, the default udp://1.1.1.1 will work fine most of the time. However, if the internet stops
          working suddenly, try changing this to tcp://1.1.1.1 or 8.8.8.8. This is especially true while on 4G/5G
          networks.
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr />

      <section id="updates" class={sectionStyle}>
        <h1 class={headingStyle}>App updates</h1>
        <p class={paragraphStyle}>
          As a last resort, under the About section, you can update the app itself. It is extremely rare that the app
          will require an update, 99% of the time it is the server, or during Chinese holidays.
        </p>
        <img src="/tips/update.png" alt="update" width={imageWidth} class="self-center" loading="lazy" />

        <p class={paragraphStyle}>
          You can also try updating your profile by pressing the refresh button on the main page. Occasionally, I will
          push out updates in case things stop working.
        </p>
        <img src="/tips/refresh.png" alt="update" width={imageWidth / 1.5} class="self-center" loading="lazy" />
      </section>

      <hr />

      <section id="mobile" class={sectionStyle}>
        <h1 class={headingStyle}>Mobile-only tips</h1>
        <p class={paragraphStyle}>
          This feature is only available on mobile. Under Settings > Advanced > Per-App Proxy. If you have mainly
          Chinese apps, select 'Proxy only selected apps" and pick which apps to use the VPN like Google/Youtube.
          <br />
          <br />
          However, if you mainly have US/international apps, choose "Do not proxy selected apps" and pick those apps like
          Alipay/WeChat. This way you can avoid constantly turning the VPN on/off.
        </p>
        <img src="/tips/per-app.png" alt="pre-app" width={imageWidth} class="self-center" loading="lazy" />
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</DashboardLayout>
